main event: Two silver sphere-shaped objects were observed moving in a straight line to the west over Peoria, Illinois.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for two hours,One object was reported to be 5 miles behind the other,One of the objects appeared to have a red light on it,Visual observation was conducted with 7-power binoculars,The objects were observed in darkness and behind clouds.
witness description: Officer McNamara Jerome J., 1/LT Duty Director, reported no radar contact and visual contact from the station.
